1
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:34,130
- Good morning.

2
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,923
Hello.

3
00:02:35,948 --> 00:02:38,617
You're not thinking
of going to work today, are you?

4
00:02:38,743 --> 00:02:40,845
Yes.

5
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:44,248
You should take
the rest of the week.

6
00:02:44,373 --> 00:02:45,891
I'm fine.

7
00:02:45,917 --> 00:02:48,335
That inhaler
seems to be doing the trick.

8
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:51,923
Yes, honey.
But you shouldn't push it.

9
00:02:52,048 --> 00:02:55,384
I want you well
for the weekend.

10
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:58,779
Mom wants to party.

11
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:00,990
It's just a little get-together.

12
00:03:01,015 --> 00:03:04,560
Just the family
and a few friends.

13
00:03:04,685 --> 00:03:10,691
We've got a lot to celebrate.
Don't you think?

14
00:03:10,816 --> 00:03:12,710
Yes, sure. Sounds good.

15
00:03:12,735 --> 00:03:14,753
Walter.

16
00:03:22,244 --> 00:03:25,998
- Do you want something else?
- No, I'm fine.

17
00:03:26,124 --> 00:03:27,808
What are you doing today?

18
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:30,811
Nothing.

19
00:03:30,836 --> 00:03:33,272
You changed your mind.

20
00:03:33,297 --> 00:03:35,315
Yes.

21
00:03:42,681 --> 00:03:45,243
If you take a good nap,

22
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:48,204
you'll have your reward tonight.

23
00:03:50,189 --> 00:03:52,166
Have a nice day.

24
00:03:52,191 --> 00:03:54,210
Thanks.

25
00:04:34,066 --> 00:04:36,501
Are you busy?

26
00:04:36,527 --> 00:04:39,130
Can we meet?

27
00:04:39,155 --> 00:04:40,547
I actually thought

28
00:04:40,572 --> 00:04:42,466
you were gone for good.

29
00:04:42,491 --> 00:04:44,326
I mean,
that you have passed away.

30
00:04:44,451 --> 00:04:45,803
I was even checking the obits.

31
00:04:45,828 --> 00:04:49,723
No such luck.

32
00:04:49,748 --> 00:04:52,226
So how are you?

33
00:04:52,251 --> 00:04:53,978
Are you still coughing up blood

34
00:04:54,003 --> 00:04:56,755
and saying you don't deserve it,
and you're an asshole?

35
00:04:56,881 --> 00:04:59,108
A little bit of both.

36
00:04:59,133 --> 00:05:01,385
I still think the same
about me.

37
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:05,597
And the cough
is there.

38
00:05:05,723 --> 00:05:08,284
What did the doctor say?

39
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:10,328
Which are the studies results?

40
00:05:10,352 --> 00:05:12,271
- Radiation pneumonitis.
Shit.

41
00:05:12,396 --> 00:05:14,648
Actually, it isn't as bad
as it sounds.

42
00:05:14,773 --> 00:05:17,317
- Yes, sure.
- Really.

43
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:20,045
It's part of the process.

44
00:05:20,071 --> 00:05:23,132
The treatment is simple.

45
00:05:23,157 --> 00:05:26,410
These are mild side
effects.

46
00:05:26,535 --> 00:05:28,012
And the cancer?

47
00:05:28,037 --> 00:05:30,472
There's good news.

48
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:32,683
Is it what I'm imagining?

49
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:34,168
The tumor isn't smaller,
is it?

50
00:05:34,293 --> 00:05:38,063
Yes, it is smaller.

51
00:05:38,089 --> 00:05:40,107
Really?

52
00:05:40,132 --> 00:05:42,693
I'm not cured,

53
00:05:42,718 --> 00:05:45,054
but there's been a significant
size reduction.

54
00:05:45,179 --> 00:05:48,240
I know you aren't cured,

55
00:05:48,266 --> 00:05:49,850
but how significant
is the reduction?

56
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:51,369
Eighty percent.

57
00:05:51,393 --> 00:05:52,895
Eighty percent?
That's a lot!

58
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:55,873
It's like three quarters.

59
00:05:55,898 --> 00:05:57,416
No.

60
00:05:57,441 --> 00:05:59,610
Three quarters would
be 75 percent.

61
00:05:59,735 --> 00:06:01,586
So it's a little bit more.

62
00:06:01,612 --> 00:06:03,088
Even better!

63
00:06:03,114 --> 00:06:05,632
Cancer is still there,

64
00:06:05,657 --> 00:06:09,094
but I have options now.

65
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,871
That's the word they used
"options."

66
00:06:10,996 --> 00:06:13,015
It's great, man!

67
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:16,476
I know you aren't an optimist.

68
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:19,171
But you have
plenty to celebrate.

69
00:06:19,297 --> 00:06:21,190
I know why I'm saying it.

70
00:06:21,215 --> 00:06:23,483
I rather be prudent.

71
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:26,345
My grandmother
didn't even make it

72
00:06:26,470 --> 00:06:28,322
to the phase you are now.

73
00:06:28,347 --> 00:06:30,324
We never thought

74
00:06:30,349 --> 00:06:31,850
that the tumor
could be reduced.

75
00:06:31,976 --> 00:06:34,937
In my case, it's smaller.
Unbelievable.

76
00:06:35,062 --> 00:06:36,997
But I have to admit it.

77
00:06:37,022 --> 00:06:38,582
It's much smaller now.

78
00:06:38,607 --> 00:06:40,209
You did it, man!

79
00:06:40,234 --> 00:06:42,169
You should be celebrating!

80
00:06:42,194 --> 00:06:43,962
Let's have some brandy.

81
00:06:43,988 --> 00:06:45,381
Easy, easy.

82
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:46,757
Now what?

83
00:06:46,782 --> 00:06:52,288
No, no,
hold on, hold on.

84
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:54,539
That's your part
from the selling

85
00:06:54,665 --> 00:06:56,375
of the production
while you weren't here.

86
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:57,835
Do we still have
stock?

87
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:00,838
Yes, we do.
But it won't last much.

88
00:07:00,963 --> 00:07:03,757
- It sells like hotcakes.
- Great.

89
00:07:07,928 --> 00:07:09,863
Considering this big news,

90
00:07:09,888 --> 00:07:11,907
what are we going to do?

91
00:07:11,932 --> 00:07:13,642
I don't want you to think
I'm pushing you.

92
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:15,577
Not at all, but--

93
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:19,664
Yes, yes. I know.

94
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:21,359
I think
we should stay cautious.

95
00:07:21,483 --> 00:07:23,461
Let's sell off what we have.

96
00:07:23,485 --> 00:07:27,506
Then, we'll...

97
00:07:27,531 --> 00:07:30,450
Say it, man.
Don't worry.

98
00:07:30,575 --> 00:07:32,703
Jose, you know
I got into this

99
00:07:32,828 --> 00:07:35,539
because I was dying,
because I was very bad.

100
00:07:35,664 --> 00:07:38,125
I had nothing
to leave to my family.

101
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:40,144
You aren't dying now, are you?

102
00:07:40,169 --> 00:07:42,896
I hope so.

103
00:07:42,921 --> 00:07:44,631
I think it would be
very irresponsible

104
00:07:44,756 --> 00:07:45,966
if we stay in
this business,

105
00:07:46,091 --> 00:07:47,567
which is too risky.

106
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:49,611
Circumstances have changed.

107
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:55,684
You know you may disappear
in this business overnight.

108
00:07:55,726 --> 00:08:00,564
Then, you're saying
you made up your mind.

109
00:08:00,605 --> 00:08:02,291
I think it's the best.

110
00:08:02,316 --> 00:08:06,695
Let's sell what we have,
and we're done.

111
00:08:11,116 --> 00:08:15,620
The first thing they do
is to cool the glasses.

112
00:08:15,662 --> 00:08:19,291
Then, they add
some salt here

113
00:08:19,417 --> 00:08:22,019
to improve the taste.

114
00:08:22,044 --> 00:08:24,062
Look! It's done!

115
00:08:24,088 --> 00:08:25,923
- How...?
- The salt...

116
00:08:26,048 --> 00:08:28,733
Sorry to interrupt.

117
00:08:28,759 --> 00:08:31,303
Can I make a toast
with a non-alcoholic beverage?

118
00:08:31,429 --> 00:08:36,725
If you're carrying
quintuplets, you can.

119
00:08:36,850 --> 00:08:42,498
Let's make a toast, then.

120
00:08:42,564 --> 00:08:46,277
I know one party
can't begin to repay

121
00:08:46,402 --> 00:08:51,198
all the love and support
you've given us.

122
00:08:51,323 --> 00:08:53,533
Therefore,
we have a bartender

123
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:55,219
who came from Mexico.

124
00:08:55,244 --> 00:08:56,720
Bravo!

125
00:08:56,745 --> 00:08:58,763
He learnt to prepare margaritas.

126
00:08:58,789 --> 00:09:03,210
If there's sadness,
fill up your glass.

127
00:09:03,335 --> 00:09:06,646
In case of happiness...

128
00:09:06,671 --> 00:09:09,941
- Your glass fill up!

129
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:12,069
Okay!

130
00:09:12,094 --> 00:09:17,766
I really want to thank you,
all of you.

131
00:09:17,808 --> 00:09:24,606
These last few months
have been... hard

132
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:31,213
to put it mildly.

133
00:09:31,238 --> 00:09:34,741
Walter has come through it
like a champ.

134
00:09:34,866 --> 00:09:36,843
Honey, I'm proud of you.

135
00:09:36,868 --> 00:09:38,845
Thank you.

136
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:41,890
We all are.

137
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:47,754
For the first time,
we look at the future

138
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:49,940
optimistically.

139
00:09:49,965 --> 00:09:52,610
I want to thank two persons

140
00:09:52,634 --> 00:09:55,695
who couldn't be here today.

141
00:09:55,720 --> 00:10:00,242
They are Edgar and Marcela.

142
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:03,145
For those of you
who don't know them,

143
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:06,248
they're very generous people.

144
00:10:06,273 --> 00:10:10,027
They paid
for Walter's treatment.

145
00:10:10,152 --> 00:10:11,670
Without them,

146
00:10:11,695 --> 00:10:13,489
I don't know
what we'd have done.

147
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:15,591
They're our angels.

148
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:18,009
To Edgar and Marcela.

149
00:10:18,035 --> 00:10:21,054
- Cheers!

150
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:23,765
We want to hear the king!

151
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,392
Tell your father!

152
00:10:25,417 --> 00:10:28,395
Come on, Dad. Speech.

153
00:10:28,420 --> 00:10:30,772
I'm not good at this.

154
00:10:30,797 --> 00:10:33,817
Come on!

155
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:40,282
Well, what can I say?

156
00:10:40,307 --> 00:10:45,454
When I got my diagnosis,

157
00:10:45,479 --> 00:10:51,318
the first thing I thought
was "Why me?"

158
00:10:51,443 --> 00:10:54,254
Now that I got the good news

159
00:10:54,279 --> 00:10:56,965
that I'm much better

160
00:10:56,990 --> 00:11:00,244
that I'm getting better
every day,

161
00:11:00,369 --> 00:11:04,164
I wonder the same thing:
Why me?

162
00:11:10,962 --> 00:11:13,131
Thank you for coming.

163
00:11:10,962 --> 00:11:15,942
Cheers!

164
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:18,803
Those were inspiring
words.

165
00:11:22,974 --> 00:11:25,810
He's as cold
as ice.

166
00:11:29,565 --> 00:11:31,500
I have to admit it.

167
00:11:31,525 --> 00:11:32,959
They are original.

168
00:11:32,984 --> 00:11:34,461
Pay attention:

169
00:11:34,486 --> 00:11:37,088
They made a mercury switch bomb,

170
00:11:37,114 --> 00:11:39,132
add it a 9-volt battery,

171
00:11:39,157 --> 00:11:42,286
and use
less than eight ounces of C-4.

172
00:11:42,411 --> 00:11:43,845
And there's more.

173
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,472
They take the man's head,

174
00:11:45,497 --> 00:11:48,726
and put it on a turtle.

175
00:11:48,750 --> 00:11:50,686
Don't say they aren't original.

176
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:52,187
Why a turtle, uncle?

177
00:11:52,212 --> 00:11:53,689
That's the best part.

178
00:11:53,713 --> 00:11:57,092
They use the turtle
as... not a metaphor,

179
00:11:57,134 --> 00:11:59,361
not an analogy either.

180
00:11:59,386 --> 00:12:02,889
What's the word
I'm looking for, Walter?

181
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:04,616
Well, whatever.

182
00:12:04,642 --> 00:12:07,018
The point
is that the man we had there,

183
00:12:07,144 --> 00:12:08,646
our snitch,
was called Tortuga or Turtle.

184
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:12,149
I don't know why.
He resembled a mandrill

185
00:12:12,274 --> 00:12:14,167
more than a turtle.

186
00:12:14,192 --> 00:12:15,986
That was
the beginning of everything.

187
00:12:16,111 --> 00:12:18,213
Can I have one?

188
00:12:18,238 --> 00:12:20,949
I know what the word
I've been looking for is.

189
00:12:21,074 --> 00:12:22,593
Poetic!

190
00:12:22,618 --> 00:12:25,996
They use the turtle
in a poetic manner.

191
00:12:26,121 --> 00:12:28,098
Do you understand?

192
00:12:36,923 --> 00:12:38,358
Cheers!

193
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:39,859
Come on, drink it.

194
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:41,637
Wait until your mother
doesn't see you.

195
00:12:41,761 --> 00:12:43,739
Drink it, drink it.

196
00:12:51,647 --> 00:12:53,691
No, uncle.
It's too bitter.

197
00:12:53,815 --> 00:12:55,917
Let me see.

198
00:12:55,942 --> 00:12:57,919
He's growing a beard.

199
00:12:57,944 --> 00:12:59,504
You have some down here.

200
00:12:59,530 --> 00:13:03,742
It was about time
you became a man.

201
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:05,885
No, uncle.

202
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,078
Uncle,
is there a worm there?

203
00:13:07,204 --> 00:13:08,722
No, no, no.

204
00:13:08,747 --> 00:13:10,457
Mezcal is the one
that has a worm.

205
00:13:10,582 --> 00:13:11,833
This is tequila,
not mezcal.

206
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:13,560
It gives you a hangover.

207
00:13:13,585 --> 00:13:15,353
I went to Cartagena once

208
00:13:15,379 --> 00:13:16,814
for a practice,

209
00:13:16,838 --> 00:13:18,882
and after the practice,
the instructor

210
00:13:19,007 --> 00:13:21,259
takes a bottle of mezcal,
and we started drinking.

211
00:13:21,385 --> 00:13:24,304
By my fourth mezcal,
I couldn't even think.

212
00:13:24,429 --> 00:13:26,682
But the man didn't stop
until he ate the worm.

213
00:13:26,806 --> 00:13:28,726
Come on,
poor me some.

214
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:34,064
He didn't stop.
He ate it.

215
00:13:34,189 --> 00:13:36,625
Hey, Walter!

216
00:13:36,650 --> 00:13:39,085
What are you doing?

217
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:41,363
What do you think
I'm doing?

218
00:13:41,488 --> 00:13:43,214
He's only fifteen.

219
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:46,034
Do you want to be
the father of the year?

220
00:13:49,496 --> 00:13:52,249
Why do you look at him.
We're celebrating.

221
00:14:01,383 --> 00:14:03,360
All of it.

222
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:16,398
It's okay.
Don't worry.

223
00:14:16,523 --> 00:14:19,901
Hey, hey, no, no, no.
It's enough.

224
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:24,489
- Walter!
- Drink all of it!

225
00:14:29,494 --> 00:14:32,430
I wouldn't have drunk that.

226
00:14:40,839 --> 00:14:42,816
I think people

227
00:14:42,841 --> 00:14:44,317
are drinking too m--

228
00:14:44,342 --> 00:14:47,387
Henry, give me the
bottle!

229
00:14:47,512 --> 00:14:50,474
Do you know what?
No!

230
00:14:50,599 --> 00:14:53,017
These are my house,
my son, and my
bottle.

231
00:14:53,143 --> 00:14:54,394
Give it
to me!

232
00:14:54,519 --> 00:14:57,539
Calm down. Easy.

233
00:14:59,858 --> 00:15:02,653
You've heard me.
Give it to me.

234
00:15:05,196 --> 00:15:10,134
Everything is okay.

235
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:13,597
What happened?

236
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:21,672
My dear, my dear.
It's okay.

237
00:15:21,797 --> 00:15:25,442
What happened?

238
00:15:25,467 --> 00:15:28,303
- I can't believe it.
- What?

239
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:33,617
It's okay, honey.

240
00:15:33,642 --> 00:15:37,479
- Water?
- Yes.

241
00:15:37,604 --> 00:15:42,417
What did you drink?

242
00:15:42,442 --> 00:15:45,236
You bring him in,
I'll get the water.

243
00:16:14,516 --> 00:16:16,284
Ups!

244
00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:19,270
You weren't supposed to
wake up.

245
00:16:19,396 --> 00:16:20,956
Ever?

246
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:22,858
No, I was just
thinking

247
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:24,234
I'd bring you breakfast
to bed.

248
00:16:24,359 --> 00:16:26,110
Do you want me
to go back to bed?

249
00:16:26,236 --> 00:16:27,987
No, it isn't
worth it.

250
00:16:28,112 --> 00:16:29,547
Can I help you?

251
00:16:29,573 --> 00:16:31,008
No, I got it.

252
00:16:31,032 --> 00:16:33,844
Just have a seat over there.

253
00:16:33,869 --> 00:16:35,913
- Here?
- Yes.

254
00:16:36,037 --> 00:16:38,749
Let's see how it tastes.
Is there any coffee?

255
00:16:41,710 --> 00:16:43,712
Coffee!
I knew I was missing something.

256
00:16:43,837 --> 00:16:45,229
It'll be right there.

257
00:16:45,255 --> 00:16:46,690
No, I'll do it.

258
00:16:46,715 --> 00:16:48,550
No!
You won't do anything.

259
00:16:48,675 --> 00:16:50,844
- Just stay there.
- Okay. I'll stay here.

260
00:16:50,969 --> 00:16:53,154
Let's see how it tastes.

261
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:54,514
What did you
cook?

262
00:16:54,639 --> 00:16:57,935
You'll see.
It's a surprise.

263
00:16:58,059 --> 00:17:00,979
- Surprise.
- Let's see.

264
00:17:01,104 --> 00:17:06,777
It's<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif"> huevos rancheros</font></i>
with sausage.

265
00:17:06,902 --> 00:17:12,115
Yes, there're many
sausages.

266
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,675
Try them.

267
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:17,012
Can I have a fork?

268
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:19,790
It's hard to eat them
without a fork. Right.

269
00:17:25,378 --> 00:17:26,964
Do you have to
work today?

270
00:17:27,088 --> 00:17:29,132
Whatever that means
to you.

271
