498
00:31:39,732 --> 00:31:41,166
So?

499
00:31:41,191 --> 00:31:44,211
What do you mean?

500
00:31:44,236 --> 00:31:46,213
What did you want me to say?

501
00:31:46,238 --> 00:31:48,073
"Dad, meet my lazy
neighbor.

502
00:31:48,198 --> 00:31:52,119
All he does is fuck me
all the time."

503
00:31:52,161 --> 00:31:54,931
That's all we do,

504
00:31:54,955 --> 00:31:56,974
don't we?

505
00:32:00,085 --> 00:32:02,797
Why do you care
what my father thinks?

506
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:04,757
I'm not talking
about your dad!

507
00:32:04,882 --> 00:32:06,233
Then what are we talking about?

508
00:32:06,258 --> 00:32:07,735
I'm talking about us!

509
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:09,512
- About us?
- Yes, you and me.

510
00:32:09,637 --> 00:32:13,616
Yo and me what?

511
00:32:23,776 --> 00:32:26,445
- Do you know what?
- Look, Jose, don't...

512
00:32:26,570 --> 00:32:29,365
- I'm out of this.
- No, come.

513
00:32:32,535 --> 00:32:38,207
- Jose!
- What?

514
00:32:38,332 --> 00:32:42,044
Don't react like this.
It isn't worth it.

515
00:32:42,169 --> 00:32:47,090
What isn't worth it?
That you're embarrassed of
me.

516
00:32:47,216 --> 00:32:48,734
It isn't that.

517
00:32:48,759 --> 00:32:51,737
So what is it?

518
00:34:25,230 --> 00:34:28,250
Dad?

519
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:34,156
- Dad?
- Down here!

520
00:34:48,921 --> 00:34:53,150
What are you doing?

521
00:34:53,175 --> 00:34:56,070
It's rotted.

522
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:58,781
What?

523
00:34:58,806 --> 00:35:04,478
Look at this.
Do you see it?

524
00:35:04,603 --> 00:35:07,564
Yes,
yes.

525
00:35:07,690 --> 00:35:09,900
- Wood?
- Wood.

526
00:35:10,026 --> 00:35:12,335
Wood with strange bodies.

527
00:35:12,361 --> 00:35:14,337
Bodies?

528
00:35:14,363 --> 00:35:16,799
Fungus.

529
00:35:16,824 --> 00:35:20,260
They're everywhere.

530
00:35:20,285 --> 00:35:21,537
I don't see
anything.

531
00:35:21,662 --> 00:35:24,056
But there they are.

532
00:35:24,081 --> 00:35:29,962
You have to know
where to look.

533
00:35:30,087 --> 00:35:32,882
Give me the lever
and the hammer.

534
00:35:33,007 --> 00:35:36,969
Yes, I'm
coming.

535
00:35:37,094 --> 00:35:39,972
We have to cut it out
and start fresh.

536
00:35:40,097 --> 00:35:42,725
Is the house
going to collapse?

537
00:35:42,850 --> 00:35:44,326
No.

538
00:35:44,351 --> 00:35:47,563
While I'm here,
put that out.

539
00:35:47,688 --> 00:35:51,792
Okay.

540
00:35:51,817 --> 00:35:54,611
The hacksaw!
Give me the hacksaw again.

541
00:36:12,254 --> 00:36:14,048
Do you think you'll have
a better salary

542
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:16,150
if you stay working late.

543
00:36:16,174 --> 00:36:20,387
- I'm going.
- Okay.

544
00:36:20,512 --> 00:36:23,390
May I ask you
something

545
00:36:23,515 --> 00:36:25,601
about Ferreterías
Don Fabio?

546
00:36:25,726 --> 00:36:28,687
Ferreterías Don Fabio?
Yes.

547
00:36:28,812 --> 00:36:31,565
It's listed as a current
asset on this balance sheet,

548
00:36:31,690 --> 00:36:35,318
but the invoice was never
presented to accounts.

549
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:37,420
God.

550
00:36:37,446 --> 00:36:41,825
I need time to analyze
my dad's stuff.

551
00:36:41,867 --> 00:36:45,054
He did business by saying:

552
00:36:45,079 --> 00:36:46,914
"Don't worry.
Pay me on Friday."

553
00:36:47,039 --> 00:36:48,765
He thought small companies

554
00:36:48,791 --> 00:36:51,393
deserved that chance.

555
00:36:51,418 --> 00:36:53,462
Tomorrow,
after having some rest,

556
00:36:53,587 --> 00:36:57,649
we'll talk about it.

557
00:36:57,674 --> 00:37:00,469
- Okay.
- Don't stay longer.

558
00:37:08,602 --> 00:37:10,037
Cielo, I'm serious.

559
00:37:10,062 --> 00:37:12,206
I don't want to leave you here.

560
00:37:19,488 --> 00:37:23,700
What happened?
Are you okay?

561
00:37:25,911 --> 00:37:28,205
Ye's, I'm fine.
Don't worry.

562
00:37:28,330 --> 00:37:29,706
It's the
hormones.

563
00:37:29,832 --> 00:37:33,043
It happens all the time.
You can go.

564
00:37:33,169 --> 00:37:36,730
No, I won't leave you here.

565
00:37:39,758 --> 00:37:45,072
What's the matter?

566
00:37:45,097 --> 00:37:50,477
I think I don't see
the difference.

567
00:37:50,602 --> 00:37:52,246
I don't understand.

568
00:37:52,270 --> 00:37:55,249
After the good news

569
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:59,295
about Walter's health,

570
00:37:59,319 --> 00:38:03,115
I thought things would
change.

571
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:06,760
But it's all the same.

572
00:38:06,785 --> 00:38:09,371
I thought I was going
to find the light

573
00:38:09,496 --> 00:38:10,914
at the end of the tunnel,
but...

574
00:38:11,040 --> 00:38:15,811
The tunnel goes on.

575
00:38:15,836 --> 00:38:17,295
- Look, I...
- I'm sorry.

576
00:38:17,420 --> 00:38:20,799
I shouldn't be bothering
you.

577
00:38:20,924 --> 00:38:23,902
Don't worry.

578
00:38:23,927 --> 00:38:26,404
I understand you.

579
00:38:26,429 --> 00:38:29,241
I went through a very hard time.

580
00:38:29,266 --> 00:38:32,244
It was a virus.

581
00:38:32,269 --> 00:38:34,288
Once my father

582
00:38:34,312 --> 00:38:36,690
was at the clinic,
before dying.

583
00:38:36,815 --> 00:38:41,611
When he finally was dismissed.
I got sick.

584
00:38:41,737 --> 00:38:43,213
It was a very strong virus.

585
00:38:43,239 --> 00:38:45,257
I couldn't move from bed.

586
00:38:45,282 --> 00:38:47,467
I couldn't stop thinking "why?"

587
00:38:47,492 --> 00:38:48,911
He's at home.
Why I can't be with him?

588
00:38:49,036 --> 00:38:52,581
Why was I there,
and not with him?

589
00:38:52,706 --> 00:38:55,309
I think some time,

590
00:38:55,333 --> 00:38:58,812
when I could relax,

591
00:38:58,837 --> 00:39:01,190
my defenses went low.

592
00:39:01,215 --> 00:39:03,717
When you're the strongest
at home,

593
00:39:03,842 --> 00:39:06,778
you're more tired than anybody.

594
00:40:48,947 --> 00:40:51,007
Aren't you going to work?

595
00:40:51,033 --> 00:40:54,703
No, there're
fungi.

596
00:40:54,828 --> 00:40:58,540
There're fungi everywhere,
rotting everything.

597
00:41:06,298 --> 00:41:09,176
I have to
continue.

598
00:43:00,870 --> 00:43:06,851
Okay. Bye.

599
00:43:00,870 --> 00:43:03,806
I'll call you.

600
00:43:21,308 --> 00:43:25,287
My God!

601
00:43:25,312 --> 00:43:27,147
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

602
00:43:27,272 --> 00:43:29,732
- Yes, yes, yes.
- No, hold on.

603
00:43:29,858 --> 00:43:32,835
I'll take that.

604
00:43:44,540 --> 00:43:47,376
Thank you.
It's a shame.

605
00:44:40,554 --> 00:44:44,407
You shouldn't buy those matches.

606
00:44:44,433 --> 00:44:45,950
What?

607
00:44:45,975 --> 00:44:48,895
These matches
are the wrong kind.

608
00:44:49,020 --> 00:44:51,106
Red phosphorous is found
in the striker strips

609
00:44:51,231 --> 00:44:52,957
not in the matches themselves.

610
00:44:52,982 --> 00:44:54,459
Get some boxes

611
00:44:54,484 --> 00:44:57,962
that guarantee more surface.

612
00:44:57,987 --> 00:44:59,464
Something else.

613
00:44:59,489 --> 00:45:01,241
Don't buy everything
in the same place.

614
00:45:01,366 --> 00:45:02,842
Buy in different places

615
00:45:02,867 --> 00:45:05,912
so that
we attract less attention.

616
00:45:06,037 --> 00:45:08,831
- Are you following me?
- Yes, sure.

617
00:45:38,987 --> 00:45:40,422
I ran away.

618
00:45:40,447 --> 00:45:42,298
You're so silly.

619
00:45:42,324 --> 00:45:44,217
We don't have time

620
00:45:44,242 --> 00:45:45,594
to waste in silly things.

621
00:45:45,619 --> 00:45:48,597
That's the man.

622
00:45:58,256 --> 00:46:01,234
Stay out of my territory.

